  "prompt": "What's your review on harry potter and the cursed child?",
  "response": "\"Harry Potter and the Cursed Child\" is a play written by Jack Thorne, based on an original story by J.K. Rowling, John Tiffany, and Thorne. It premiered in London's West End in 2016, and has since been staged in various locations worldwide.\n\nThe play serves as a continuation of the Harry Potter series, set 19 years after the events of \"Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows\". It follows Harry Potter, now a Ministry of Magic employee, and focuses on his son, Albus Severus Potter, who struggles with the weight of his family's legacy.\n\nReception of the play has been mixed. Many fans appreciate the opportunity to revisit the Wizarding World and to see beloved characters in a new light. The play is praised for its stunning stagecraft and impressive special effects, which bring magic to life in a theatrical setting.\n\nHowever, some fans and critics feel that the storyline doesn't fully capture the spirit of the original books, with criticism often focused on character developments and plot choices that seem inconsistent with the established world. The decision to present the story as a play rather than a novel has also been a point of debate, as the format naturally limits the depth of narrative and world-building compared to the original books.\n\nOverall, \"Harry Potter and the Cursed Child\" offers a unique and visually captivating experience, especially for those who have the chance to see it performed live. However, opinions on the story itself are divided, with its reception largely dependent on individual expectations and attachment to the original series.",
